{
  "name": "Dowsing",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "modules/pf1spheres/assets/icons/spheres/divination.webp",
  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You may spend a spell point to divine the location of a creature or object within range. This may be a specific creature or object or a kind of creature or object, but either way you must have a clear mental image of the creature or object to divine for it (thus, you could not divine broadly for traps, creatures of a broad creature type, etc.). If divining for a kind of creature or object, you only locate the closest item of that kind. This method of using divine is not blocked by wood or stone, but is still blocked by lead.</p>\n",
